/* ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   SCALE CODING — IMPORTANT
   Exit survey uses TWO scale types:
   SATISFACTION items (cols: coop_dept, coop_other, job_training,
     resources, pmi, training_prog, pay, career, phys_conditions,
     get_resources): 1=Very Poor/Dissatisfied → 4=Excellent/Very Satisfied
     Risk signal: low score = high risk → contribution = weight*(4−x)

   AGREEMENT items (all remaining cols — positive statements about
     supervisor, culture, safety, communication):
     1=Strongly Agree (positive outcome) → 4=Strongly Disagree
     Risk signal: high score = disagrees with positive = high risk
     → contribution = weight*(x−1)

   Calibrated from actual WYDOT exit survey means (n=307 leavers):
   Pay=1.95, Career=2.13, PMI=2.26 (low SAT scores → high risk) ✓
